  "body": "### Description\nAs an node operator, I'd like to use R1 curves and the sub command to precreate keys doesn't appear to support this https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/latest/Reference/CLI/CLI-Subcommands/#export_1\n\nIn doing the https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/latest/Reference/CLI/CLI-Subcommands/#generate-blockchain-config I can get the validators to have R1 nodekeys prefectly fine and when a node starts up clean, it looks at the genesis and can generate an R1 compatible nodekey but the subcommand needs an extra arg\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\nHave an R1 nodekey generated by the `export` subcommand\n\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\n1. Create an R1 network\n2. Create a nodekey using ` .../bin/besu public-key export --to=public.key` \n3. Use the new nodekey from step 2 for a new node that joins the network in step 1 and it'll fail with Breach_of_protocol errors\n\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\nExpect that the nodekey would work for the R1 network\n\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\nNode doesn't join the network and has Breach_of_protocol errors in the logs\n\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\n100% \n\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\n* Software version: [`besu --version`] 21.10.2 +\n* Java version: [`java -version`] jdk11\n* OS Name & Version: [`cat /etc/*release`] ubuntu 20.04lts\n* Kernel Version: [`uname -a`] linux 5.11\n* Virtual Machine software & version: [`vmware -v`] n/a\n* Docker Version: [`docker version`] n/a same behaviour natively \n* Cloud VM, type, size: [Amazon Web Services I3-large] n/a\n\n### Additional Information\n\n### Tasks\n* Add curve type to the public key subcommand. Keep \n* Update KeyPairUtil to log what curve we are using when creating a new public key\n\nHint: Take a look at GenerateBlockchainConfig processEcCurve",
